rComments: This class is probably one of the easiest in the entire university. The professor definitely taught a linguistic  perspective which I found dry and hard to follow without a background in languages. However, he made a huge effort to give students as many points as possible on tests and quizzes so it was literally impossible to fail.

David is an unassuming, intelligent, and dedicated professor. He made Gaelic all the more interesting with his stories, songs, and quotes. His primary knowledge of the Gaelic speaking world was incredible, as was his knowledge of different dialects. My only complaint was that I wished there had been some grammar on the quizes.. but that's just me.
This professor makes the course so much more enjoyable.
Language courses are hard even with the best professors, so I give him credit for teaching Gaelic so well.
